        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        TOp 10 Singles of the year so far: - Week 14
        1 (1) Kid Laroi - Without You 899 (855)
        2 (2) Shane Codd - Get Out Of My Head 866 (836)

        3 (5) Tiesto - The Business 856 (786)

        4 (3) Meduza/Dermot Kennedy - Paradise 843 (809)

        5 (4) Olivia Rodrigo - Driver's License 837 (788)

        6 (6) Travis Scott/HVME - Goosebumps 773 (731)

        7 (8) Anne-Marie/KSI/Digital Farm Animals - Don't Play 772 (705)

        8 (11) Nathan Evans - Wellerman 739 (665)

        9 (10) Justin Bieber - Anyone 733 (682)

        10 (7) Ed Sheeran - Afterglow 712 (712)

        Weeknd is close and climbing with 2 records: Save Your Tears and Blinding Lights. A big drop from Kid Laroi next week could see Tiesto be the #1 of the year so far. Yes, Olivia Rodrigo fell this week, but should regain the place by overtaking Paradise, especially if she retains the 15-position difference of this week.
        Wellerman makes it's debut in the year's top 10. Being only 10 weeks old (the newest of the top 10), it is at it's highest possible position. 10 weeks at #1 earning 750 pts would not make it any higher on the chart of the year.
